            <h1 class="project-title">Dominican Republic Clinic</h1>

            <img class="img-responsive article-img pull-right" src="images/project-pics/dominican/dominican1.jpg">

            <p>World Spine Care is currently working on the development of a project in the town of Moca in the Dominican Republic.</p>

            <h3>The Project aims to:</h3>

            <ul>
              <li>Perform an epidemiological study to determine the impact of Spinal Diseases;</li>
              <li>Disorders in designated rural or underserved communities;</li>
              <li>Identify health care resources in rural and underserved communities, which could be considered in the establishment of an evidence-based Spine care program;</li>
              <li>Establish Spine Care Centers in rural or underserved communities in Dominican Republic;</li>
              <li>Recruit volunteer health care professionals to provide primary Spine care; and</li>
              <li>Ensure interaction of health professionals with local care providers and traditional healers to share knowledge on the assessment and management of spinal problems and harmonize treatment efforts.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>The expected outcomes of the Project are:</h3>

            <ul>
              <li>Improved health and healthcare of people with Spinal Disorders and Injuries in rural and underserved communities;</li>
              <li>Trained and skilled individuals on Spine care from the targeted rural and underserved communities; and</li>
              <li>Ongoing and sustainable Spine care in the targeted rural and underserved communities and the establishment of similar programs in other communities.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>The initial Project target area are:</h3>

            <ul>
              <li>Moca; and</li>
              <li>Cayetano Germosen.</li>
            </ul>
